.TH "TransformStreamDefaultController.desiredSize" "JS" "April 22, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
TransformStreamDefaultController.desiredSize \-
TransformStreamDefaultController: desiredSize property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]desiredSize\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]TransformStreamDefaultController\f[R] interface returns the
desired size to fill the queue of the associated
\f[CR]ReadableStream\f[R].
.PP
The internal queue of a \f[CR]ReadableStream\f[R] contains chunks that
have been enqueued, but not yet read.
The browser determines the \f[B]desired size\f[R] to fill the stream,
and it is this value returned by the \f[CR]desiredSize\f[R] property.
.PP
If the \f[CR]desiredSize\f[R] is \f[CR]0\f[R] then the queue is full.
Therefore you can use this information to manually apply backpressure to
manage the queue.
.SH VALUE
The desired size.
.SH EXAMPLES
In the next example the \f[CR]desiredSize\f[R] is logged to the console.
.IP
.EX
console.log(controller.desiredSize);
.EE
